The switch has been flipped on the Johannesburg Zoo's enchanting festival of lights. Twitter/@JoburgParksZoo JOHANNESBURG - The switch has been flipped on the Johannesburg Zoo's enchanting festival of lights. 
That's due to the heightened lockdown announced earlier this week. The festival was sold out until the 03 January. READ: Cape Town celebrates 50th Festival of Lights But organisers say all ticket buyers will be refunded. It is yet another blow to the tourism and arts industries as over a hundred artists were scheduled to perform. In the meantime, the Joburg Theatre will stream performances of the 'Sleeping Beauty' pantomime, on its Facebook page.